{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "64b16aa6f23ac7d519f9b65a", "type": "multipleCorrect", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 210, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76cfc52ffa3c944600e0"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fec2b295b085ab6eb91"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64b1672d25f94b8a85b91cda", "title": "JEE Advanced 2023 (Paper 2)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "<p>An annular disk of mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>, inner radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and outer radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> is placed on a horizontal surface with coefficient of friction <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi></math>, as shown in the figure. At some time, an impulse <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mover><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8743;</mo></mover></math>&nbsp;is applied at a height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>&nbsp;above the center of the disk. If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;then the disk rolls without slipping along the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis. Which of the following statement(s) is(are) correct?</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/a0315bc6-1fb8-4ce8-a034-ddcaf52e88b8.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 170px;\" /></p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "Yox7Z", "text": "For&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "T6iGP", "text": "For&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "nzVQg", "text": "For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></math>, the initial angular velocity does not depend on the inner radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "JoHj2", "text": "For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, the wheel always slides without rolling", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>As we know,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>J</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8710;</mo><mover><mi>P</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math></p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/653eae2f-7d86-4ac1-be2a-344654fad9e8.png\" style=\"width: 349px; height: 231px;\" /></p><p>About center of the disk, we can also write</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></msub><mi>&#969;</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>If&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mtext>pure&#160;rolling</mtext></mfenced></math></p><p>From equation(ii), we can write</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>By dividing equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;with the&nbsp;equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>iii</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Now, considering all cases:</p><p>If&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>If&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p><p>If&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#969;</mi></math>&nbsp;is independent of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>(As we get&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></math>)</p><p>If&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>and</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo></math>Wheel will&nbsp;slide without rolling.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "54d74ba4f7864c83870a20efbfeb9dde", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/eFMiMqAf6vQRE.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/eFMiMqAf6vQRE.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "64c7e8e829737784b294e469", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2